==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Copulate
<hw>Cop"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>copulatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>copulare</ets> to couple, fr.
<ets>copula</ets>. See <er>Copula</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Joined;
associated; coupled.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>Joining subject and predicate;
copulative.</def> <rj><au>F. A. March.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copulate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Copulate
<hw>Cop"u*late</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Copulated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Copulating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To unite in sexual
intercourse; to come together in the act of generation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copulation</ent>⟦br⟧
